issue.title: airodump-ng wifi6e (6ghz) "band" argument support
issue.body:
Hello, I saw in aircrack-ng v1.7 changelog that 6ghz feature was added. I tested it and yeah, my wifi6e card airodump scan is now hopping through new channels, but what I miss is a configuration argument to handle this in the same way can be done for 5ghz. I mean the "--band" argument for the airodump command line.

--band bg -> for 2.4ghz
--band abg -> for 5ghz
--band xxxx <- something for 6ghz

It could be nice to have this feature for the near future. That will allow to the scripters like me to handle this new band in the same way. Thanks.

issue.title: Add 'band 6' to airodump-ng for WiFi 6E 6GHz channels
issue.body:
# Details

WiFi 6E added a bunch of channels in the 6GHz band. Some work has already been done to allow these channels by frequency (#2273), but we need to add the channel numbers as well. 

Plus there might be some work needed in osdep and aireplay-ng.

## Related

#2205

comment.body:
In my case it takes 30 seconds (ALFA AWUS036AXM) to check frequencies

`sudo airodump-ng -a -C 5935-7115 wlan0mon`

More annoying though, is that the output lists my access point which is on 2.4 GHz (channel 1)

I'm running aircrack 1.7

issue.title: test-wpapsk-cmac regression on arm64/armhf/armel
issue.body:
I've recently packaged a git snapshot of aircrack-ng for Debian (at the current HEAD https://github.com/aircrack-ng/aircrack-ng/commit/4bf83f1a7631d6721c17a35597d2f71b35ff30bf), and stumbled upon failures when building for `arm64`/`armhf`/`armel`.

The `check` target fails when running the test `test-wpapsk-cmac`.

I've ran git bisect on the tree and found the commit that introduces the regression:
https://github.com/aircrack-ng/aircrack-ng/commit/5e8ed78e8abdb0baf5b78d42e6be4c752b512a35

Looking at the current open issues/PRs, I can see one that might be related to this issue, but I haven't tested it:
https://github.com/aircrack-ng/aircrack-ng/issues/2553
https://github.com/aircrack-ng/aircrack-ng/pull/2554

## Contents of `test-suite.log` (only the important bits)

## Debian build logs
https://buildd.debian.org/status/package.php?p=aircrack-ng
https://buildd.debian.org/status/fetch.php?pkg=aircrack-ng&arch=arm64&ver=1%3A1.7%2Bgit20230807.4bf83f1a-1&stamp=1691438883&raw=0
https://buildd.debian.org/status/fetch.php?pkg=aircrack-ng&arch=armel&ver=1%3A1.7%2Bgit20230807.4bf83f1a-1&stamp=1691439285&raw=0
https://buildd.debian.org/status/fetch.php?pkg=aircrack-ng&arch=armhf&ver=1%3A1.7%2Bgit20230807.4bf83f1a-1&stamp=1691439374&raw=0

## Script used to bisect
```
#!/bin/bash

untestable() {
    git reset --hard
    exit 125
}

fail() {
    git reset --hard
    exit 1
}

autoreconf -fiv || untestable
./configure \
    --with-gcrypt \
    --with-experimental || untestable

make -j4 || untestable

# Apply https://github.com/aircrack-ng/aircrack-ng/pull/2563 to
# add missing import.
sed -i '1s/^/#include <inttypes.h>\n/' src/airodump-ng/airodump-ng.c || untestable

# Modify makefile to only run test-wpapsk-cmac on make check.
sed -i -e "s|#am__append_1 = -liphlpapi -lsetupapi|check_PROGRAMS =  \$(am__EXEEXT_5)\nTESTS = \$(am__EXEEXT_5)\n#am__append_1 = -liphlpapi -lsetupapi|g" Makefile || untestable

# Run tests a few times to not get tricked by an issue that
# might only show up on some runs (due to parallelism).
make -j4 check || fail
touch test/unit/test-wpapsk-cmac.c
make -j4 check || fail
touch test/unit/test-wpapsk-cmac.c
make -j4 check || fail
touch test/unit/test-wpapsk-cmac.c
make -j4 check || fail
touch test/unit/test-wpapsk-cmac.c
make -j4 check || fail
touch test/unit/test-wpapsk-cmac.c

# If we got here, success.
git reset --hard
exit 0
```
